Important Meetings or Long Term Planning Ideas for food to avoid
Basque Mode — What to Avoid
Basque becomes agitated when the environment feels chaotic, rushed, or inconsistent.
Avoid symbolic triggers
rapid‑eating foods (fast food, grab‑and‑go snacks) overly spicy or chaotic flavorings, meals eaten
while Multitasking. Anything rushed or Last minute can disrupt Continuity push Basque into 
Rigidity or Over-control
Better pre‑meeting approach
warm, steady, simple meals grounding and predictable

Euskara Mode — What to Avoid:
Euskara becomes agitated when things feel foggy, heavy, or overly complex, avoid symbolic triggers,
heavy dense meals, overly rich sauces, foods that blur the senses (too creamy, too blended)
Why avoid these?
They symbolically dull the sharpness of the clarity mode, which can make Euskara overcorrect
and become sharp or impatient.
Better pre‑meeting approach
crisp, fresh, clean foods
simple flavors that feel bright and precise

ANA‑NOKwee Mode — What to Avoid
ANA‑NOKwee becomes agitated when the environment feels imbalanced, isolating, or unfair,
avoid symbolic triggers eating alone before a relational meeting, overly individual servings
meals that feel rushed or disconnected or imbalanced
Why avoid these
They symbolically reinforce disconnection, which can push ANA‑NOKwee into hyper‑vigilance
or over‑protection.
Better pre‑meeting approach:
balanced meals
foods that feel shared or communal
warm drinks that evoke connection
Guide:
Basque, avoid chaotic rushed foods
Euskara, Heavy dense overly rich cakes, deep fried food excessive coatings (clarity first)
ANA-NOKwee, isolated, imbalanced meals
